      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think drawAnimatedImage will no longer add much functionality, but it would be (slightly) simpler for a client that wants to draw it immediately:\n\n    animatedImage-\u003edraw(canvas, 0, 0, paint);\n\nvs\n\n    auto image \u003d animatedImage-\u003egetCurrentFrame();\n    canvas-\u003edrawImage(image, 0, 0, \u0026paint);\n\nThe former should only save a copy versus the latter if you don\u0027t discard |image| (or |canvas| is a type of SkCanvas that holds a reference to the SkPixelRef) before calling animatedImage-\u003edecodeNextFrame().",
